Package: Optimus
Type: Package
Title: General purpose adaptive optimisation engine
Version: 0.1.1
Author: Nicholas Andre G. Johnson [aut],
        Aleksandr B. Sahakyan [aut, cre]
Authors@R: c(person("Aleksandr B.", "Sahakyan", role=c("aut","cre"),
                    email="sahakyanlab@cantab.net"),
             person("Nicholas Andre G.", "Johnson", role="aut"))
Maintainer: Sahakyan Lab <sahakyanlab@cantab.net>
Description: This package is a general purpose optimisation engine.
    It supports i) Monte Carlo Optimisation with Metropolis Criterion
    and Acceptance Ratio Annealing on multiple cores, and ii) Acceptance
    Ratio Replica Exchange Monte Carlo Optimisation. In each case,
    the system pseudo-temperature is dynamically adjusted such that
    the observed acceptance ratio is kept near to the desired (fixed
    or changing) acceptance ratio.
License: GPL-3
URL: http://optimus.atgcdynamics.org, http://github.com/SahakyanLab/Optimus
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports:
    doParallel (>= 1.0.11),
    foreach (>= 1.4.4),
    iterators (>= 1.0.9),
    parallel (>= 3.4.2)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
NeedsCompilation: no
